    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Protective boxes with a hinged top, shaped like a thick book, for storing books, prints, pamphlets, and documents; developed in the 18th century for the storage of botanical specimens and later for the storage of books, prints, and documents.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cajas protectoras en forma de libro desarrolladas en el siglo XVIII para el almacenaje de muestras de botánica y posteriormente para almacenar libros, impresos y otros documentos. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beschermende houders in de vorm van een boek, ontwikkeld in de 18e eeuw, voor het opbergen van botanische exemplaren en later voor het opbergen van boeken, prenten en andere documenten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西元十八世紀時發明具保存功能的書本狀容器，原本用於收藏植物標本，之後亦用於收納書籍、版畫和文件。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
